unittitle_ssm: Thomas J. Burton Research Files on Manhattan Churches
abstract_ssm: This collection consists mainly of letters, clippings, bulletins, printed programs, sermons, and other ephemera related to church congregations in Manhattan. The material was collected by undertaker and historian Thomas J. Burton (1858-1920) for his book project "History of the Churches of New York, Illustrated," which was apparently never published. Related material collected by others, including E.B. Child (1846-1946), was added to the collection after it was accessioned by the New-York Historical Society.
